= Germany Joins The League of Nations

Following the outline created by the Locarno Pact, Germany has finally been allowed to join the League of Nations after years of being treated as a pariah by the Western powers. This is a significant step towards peace in the world, and certainly one towards Germany being seen as an equal by the world again.